    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify the compound that undergoes self-aldol condensation in the presence of cold dilute alkali, forming a $\\beta$-hydroxy aldehyde:</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{CHO}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Aldol condensation requires the presence of at least one $\\alpha$-hydrogen in the aldehyde. Among the options, acetaldehyde $\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}\\right)$ has $\\alpha$-hydrogens and undergoes the reaction.</p>\n<p>$$ 2 \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}+\\text { dilute } \\mathrm{NaOH}\\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}(\\mathrm{OH}) \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO} \\text { (3-hydroxy butanal) } $$</p>\n<p>This $\\beta$-hydroxy aldehyde may further dehydrate to form an $\\alpha, \\beta$-unsaturated aldehyde:</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}(\\mathrm{OH}) \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CHO} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CHCHO}+\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O} $$</p>\n<p>The other compounds either lack $\\alpha$-hydrogens or are deactivated (e.g., benzaldehyde, phenylacetylene derivative).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
