    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Which of the following compounds will undergo self aldol condensation in the presence of cold dilute alkali?",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$ \\mathrm{CH}_{2}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CHO} $"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$ \\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CHO} $"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$ \\mathrm{C}_{6} \\mathrm{H}_{5} \\mathrm{CHO} $"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$ \\mathrm{CH}_{3} \\mathrm{CH}_{2} \\mathrm{CHO} $"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Aldehydes which contain $ \\alpha $-hydrogen on a saturated carbon, i.e. $ \\mathrm{CH}_{3} \\mathrm{CH}_{2} \\mathrm{CHO} $ will undergo aldol condensation.</p><p>Although $ \\mathrm{CH}_{2}=\\stackrel{\\alpha}{\\mathrm{C}} \\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{CHO} $ also contain a $ \\alpha $-hydrogen atom but cannot be easily abstracted by a base to form a carbanion and hence does not undergo aldol condensation.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2024",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
